snippet.textDisplay:
*Re: CoVID, MS Excel, UK govt error*
== Proof Linus does no research ==

The agency tasked with collating the data was using an out of date version of Excel. They were using EXCEL 2003 which limits the number of available spreadsheets and so you have to flip between many of them. Latest versions of Excel have infinite numbers of spreadsheets available and this would NOT have happened if the UK Govt agency had been doing their jobs properly and using the most up to date software.

snippet.textDisplay:
RTX 3080 = gaming card
RTX 3090 = Titan without the actual Titan optimisations (full rate Tensor core throughput, acceleration of CAD/CAM applications), so in essence a 3080 Ti with a price higher than a 3080Ti but lower than a proper Titan
A6000 = Quadro, with all workstation optimisations enabled, ECC memory (and lots of it)...So users who were previously using Titans for CAD/CAM/AI/ML/DL will need to spring up for the A6000...

nVidia gets to fleece gaming whales with 3090, and forces workstation users to the A-series...cha-ching!
